cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with rendering realistic images with Global Illumination (GI) using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GR (Computer Graphics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as image processing is involved. The paper also uses Convolutional Autoencoders, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the denoising Neural Network used in the paper is an example of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, Radiance Caching is used, which is a technique related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
